name: Brianna Keune
personal-statement: I spent the last few years being a barista in Milwaukee while searching for a career I’m passionate about. In 2016 I decided I wanted to try my hand at creating a blog about all of my home ec knowledge. I created a WordPress site with a template, and I found that I loved trying to customize and update the template rather than write. The site never launched. I started to learn HTML by myself and found sticking to a self-learning schedule was not going to work for me. So in 2019, I joined Lambda school for it's accelerated comprehensive program and found my passion for creating APIs with a focus on how that data is presented to the audience.
